content: THAT is what happens when snakes start on the wrong side. amazingly enough, their prey does not WANT to be eaten. i gigured, once it got to the upper arms, that frog was going to ave enough. that frog was never going to be digested, dead of alive. the snake was lucky. that frog would have either been regurged within the day, or would have impacted in the snake's stomach. cool thging is, i have HEARD of snakes trying to eat a meal backwards, but until today i have never SEEN it. thanks FMI, i'll be passing this video off to the Herp society.
